latestPosts.caption:
🌸If your curls just won’t hold you’re likely missing these two non-negotiables 👇

🔬 1. Build-up = Barrier
heavy synthetic butters (like cetearyl alcohol blends), waxy oils (like coconut oil), silicones, and synthetic polymers (yes — the “plastics” like polyquaterniums) form impermeable films on your strands.
Result? Moisture can’t get in. You’re stuck needing harsh, sulfated shampoos to strip the buildup — which then stresses your scalp and strands, leading to a vicious cycle of frizz, dryness, and breakage.

💡 Tip: Choose short ingredient lists, sulfate-free cleansers, and if you spot buildup, detox your routine with plant-based, nourishing alternatives.

🧪 2. Water-Based Hold = lasting curls
Creamy products or gels made with PVP copolymers and polyquats give the illusion of hold but do nothing to hydrate or strengthen. Over time, they dry out your scalp and create flaky buildup.
Real definition comes from plant-based film formers that mimic your hair’s natural structure — sealing in moisture while allowing movement.

🌱 Go for botanical gels, not plastic ones. Your hair and scalp will thank you with shine, bounce, and real curl memory.
